FLOW SUMMARY:
1. Browser → DNS Resolution (www.google.com → IP address)
2. DNS → Firewall (checks if traffic is allowed)
3. Firewall → HTTPS Port 443 (TLS/SSL encrypted connection)
4. HTTPS → Load Balancer (distributes incoming traffic)
5. Load Balancer → Web Server (serves static content)
6. Web Server → Application Server (generates dynamic page)
7. Application Server → Database (queries/fetches data)
8. Database → Application Server (returns data)
9. Application Server → Web Server (returns complete page)
10. Web Server → Browser (serves the web page)